SIMPLE: oxy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxy-
<hw>Ox"y-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A prefix, also used
adjectively</def>, designating: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A compound containing
<xex>oxygen</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A compound containing the
<xex>hydroxyl group</xex>, more properly designated by
<xex>hydroxy-</xex>. See <er>Hydroxy-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oxy acid</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Oxyacid</er>
(below).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oxyacetic</ent>⟦br⟧
